HEADWORD: Microcrystalline
<hw>Mi`cro*crys"tal*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> + <ets>crystalline</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Crystalline on a fine, or microscopic,
scale; consisting of fine crystals; <as>as, the ground mass of certain
porphyrics is <ex>microcrystalline</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microcyte</ent>⟦br⟧
